<head1>availability</head1>
<pre>
gnome-debug: <a href="ftp://ftp.gnome.org/pub/GNOME/unstable/sources/gnome-debug/">ftp://ftp.gnome.org/pub/GNOME/unstable/sources/gnome-debug/</a>
dryad      : <a href="ftp://ftp.gnome.org/pub/GNOME/unstable/sources/dryad/">ftp://ftp.gnome.org/pub/GNOME/unstable/sources/dryad/</a>
</pre>

<p>

The latest gnome-debug sources are in the gnome cvs repository.
gnome-debug is available in the <tt>gnome-debug</tt> module, and Dryad
is available in the <tt>dryad</tt> module.  The CVS version is not
garaunteed to be stable (or to even compile), and is primarily meant
for people working on it directly.

